{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nReport §5.2 found 4/8 tickets with persisted reviews were CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED: the gate\nraised the right advisory, but the author applied it only AFTER claim — advisory latency,\nnot blindness. Authors defer advisories because nothing ranks which surviving advisories are\nworth applying *now* vs safe to defer. A deterministic triage of the round's surviving\nadvisories is pure coaching (the reviewer never writes the plan) and carries no detection\nrisk, so per the epic gate table it ships first with **no eval gate** — validated post-ship by\ndogfooding via R7's advisory-application-latency metric.\n\n## What\nAdd a **deterministic advisory-triage stage** to the Pass-4 coach path of the plan-review\ngate. It runs AFTER Pass-3 has decided findings and split them into blocking vs surviving\n(advisory), and it partitions the round's surviving **advisory** findings into two buckets —\n`apply-now` and `defer` — using ONLY fields already recorded on each decided finding. It emits\nNO new LLM judgment (no model call) and no free prose; it renders from a locked format string,\nso the same decided-finding set produces byte-identical output.\n\n**Mechanism choice (rationale).** It is NOT modelled as an entry in the Pass-4 `MOVE_REGISTRY`.\nThe move registry's schema (`review_kernel/coach.py` `MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA`) is a *per-finding*\n`{subject}`-placeholder template that the LLM fills with one bounded noun-phrase per finding; a\nsingle `{subject}` substitution structurally cannot express a ranked two-bucket split across all\nsurviving advisories, and forcing it there would require new collective-rendering logic anyway.\nSo the triage is a small pure function on the plan-review Pass-4 path, symmetric to the existing\nper-note `decision: \"block\"|\"advisory\"` stamp that `render_coach_notes` already adds — it adds a\n`triage` stamp. This keeps blast radius inside plan-review (the shared kernel coach mechanism is\nunchanged) and fits the existing architecture rather than fighting it.\n\n**The ranking rule (the core of this ticket — fully specified, grounded in real fields).**\nEvery decided finding carries `priority` (= `validity × impact`, a float in [0,1], always\npresent — `review_kernel/decide.py`) and `block_threshold` (the finding's criterion blocking\nwaterline; on the decided finding, else fall back to the registry `DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD`).\nNo other field is used — in particular there is NO \"remediation-mode carryover status\" field on\nPass-4 findings, so it is not used.\n\n- **Bucketing.** An advisory is `apply-now` iff `priority >= block_threshold - APPLY_NOW_MARGIN`\n  (i.e. it came within `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN` of blocking — highest value to apply now); otherwise\n  `defer`. `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN` is a named module constant, default **0.10**.\n- **Ordering (total, deterministic → byte-identical).** All triaged advisories are sorted by\n  `priority` DESC, then by the finding's first `criteria` id ASC, then by finding `id` ASC.\n- **Defer reason.** Each `defer` advisory carries a one-line `triage_reason` built only from its\n  own numeric fields, e.g. `deferred: priority 0.32 is 0.28 below its 0.60 block line` (fixed\n  words + the finding's recorded numbers — no LLM prose, trivially non-prescriptive).\n- **Eligibility.** Only findings with `decision == \"advisory\"` are triaged. Blocking findings\n  must be remediated regardless, so they are excluded (this is why R6 is advisory-only — it\n  resolves the earlier AC contradiction about blocking findings being \"eligible triggers\").\n\nThe triage list is attached to the plan-review coaching output (each surviving-advisory coach\nnote gains `triage` + optional `triage_reason`; advisories that mapped to no coach move still\nappear in the triage list keyed by finding id), and rendered in the review's coaching section.\nIncorporated directly into the packaged path — no config flag.\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py` — the deterministic `triage_advisories(...)` pure\n  function (bucketing + ordering + defer-reason + locked format) and its invocation on the\n  Pass-4 coach path; the `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN` constant.\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/workflow_ops.py` — wire the triage stage into the live coach-step\n  assembly so the annotation reaches the persisted verdict (`review_kernel/coach.py` touched\n  ONLY if a shared render helper turns out cleaner; default is plan-review-local, zero kernel\n  change).\n- `tests/` — unit tests pinning determinism, boundary bucketing, ordering/tie-breaks, defer-reason\n  format, and advisory-only eligibility.\n- `docs/plan-review-gate.md` — document the triage stage, the ranking rule (margin default +\n  ordering + defer-reason), and the dogfood expectation.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `triage_advisories` is byte-identical across two runs on the same fixed advisory set, and\n      its rendered text contains only fixed tokens + the findings' recorded numeric fields (no\n      LLM/prescriptive prose). Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/test_plan_review_triage.py -k determinism -q`.\n- [ ] Boundary bucketing is correct: an advisory with `priority == block_threshold - APPLY_NOW_MARGIN`\n      is `apply-now`; one epsilon below is `defer` (parametrized test). Proving command:\n      `python -m pytest tests/test_plan_review_triage.py -k boundary -q`.\n- [ ] The triaged list is ordered by `priority` DESC, tie-broken by first-criterion-id then\n      finding-id — a test with deliberate ties pins the exact order. Proving command:\n      `python -m pytest tests/test_plan_review_triage.py -k ordering -q`.\n- [ ] Only `decision == \"advisory\"` findings are triaged; blocking findings are excluded.\n      Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/test_plan_review_triage.py -k advisory_only -q`.\n- [ ] `docs/plan-review-gate.md` documents the triage stage, its ranking rule (the\n      `APPLY_NOW_MARGIN` default, the ordering, the defer-reason format), and the R7 dogfood\n      expectation (advisory-application latency observed via R7's per-criterion metric).\n- [ ] Landed through Gerrit directly in the packaged Pass-4 coach path — no config flag; `make\n      lint && make typecheck && make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784251366861816001,"uuid":"f342e3df-384f-48ba-abb9-b162949c8ddc"}